TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Multiple-Objective Programming Technique for Structuring Tax-Exempt Serial Revenue Debt Issues
AU  - Puelz, Amy v.
AU  - Lee, Sang M.
Y1  - 1992/08/01
PY  - 1992
DA  - 1992/08/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.38.8.1186
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.38.8.1186
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1186
EP  - 1200
VL  - 38
IS  - 8
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - A multiple-objective decision model to structure tax-exempt serial revenue bonds is presented in this paper. Based on goals dealing with true interest cost, marketability, debt coverage, production, and level debt, we define a goal programming model to generate a maturity schedule and coupon rate assignment for a municipal bond issue. The model is designed to be a flexible interactive decision making tool to aid in the development of a minimal-risk, cost-effective issue.
AB  - A multiple-objective decision model to structure tax-exempt serial revenue bonds is presented in this paper. Based on goals dealing with true interest cost, marketability, debt coverage, production, and level debt, we define a goal programming model to generate a maturity schedule and coupon rate assignment for a municipal bond issue. The model is designed to be a flexible interactive decision making tool to aid in the development of a minimal-risk, cost-effective issue.
